{{taxobox |image = Diploporaceae - Gyroporella.JPG | image_caption = Fossil ''Gyroporella'' from Triassic of Italy | image_width=250px | fossil_range = [[Permian]] – [[Triassic]] {{fossilrange|272.5|205.6}} | regnum = [[Plant]]ae | phylum = [[Chlorophyta]] | classis = [[Ulvophyceae]] | ordo = [[Dasycladales]] | familia = [[Triploporellaceae]] | genus = '''''Gyroporella''''' | genus_authority = [[Wilhelm von Gümbel|Gümbel]] 1872 }}
'''''Gyroporella''''' is an extinct genus of [[green algae]] in the family [[Triploporellaceae]].
==Fossil record== This genus is known in the fossil record from the [[Permian]] to the [[Triassic]] (from about 272.5 to 205.6 million years ago). Fossils of species within this genus have been found in Europe, Iran, Afghanistan, China, Malaysia and Tunisia.<ref>[http://fossilworks.org/cgi-bin/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=106984 Paleobiology Database]</ref>
