{{Infobox person | name = Holbrook Blinn | image = Holbrook Blinn in Seven Deadly Sins.png | imagesize = | caption = | birthname = | birth_date ={{Birth date|1872|1|23}} | birth_place = [[San Francisco, California]], [[United States|U.S.]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1928|6|24|1872|1|23}} | death_place = [[Croton-on-Hudson, New York]], [[United States|U.S.]] | othername = | occupation = Actor | years_active = 1897–1927 | spouse = | domesticpartner = | website = }} '''Holbrook Blinn''' (January 23, 1872 &ndash; June 24, 1928) was an [[United States|American]] stage and film actor.<ref>[https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/7317816 Holbrook Blinn; findagrave.com]</ref>
==Biography== Blinn was born in [[San Francisco, California|San Francisco]]. His father was Charles H. Blinn,<ref>[http://www.findagrave.com/cgi-bin/fg.cgi?page=gr&GSln=blinn&GSfn=charles&GSmn=h.&GSbyrel=all&GSdyrel=all&GSob=n&GRid=3521040&df=all& Charles H. Blinn; findagrave.com] Retrieved June 28, 2015</ref> a Civil War veteran and his mother Nellie Hollbrook<ref>[https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/3521041 Nellie Blinn; findagrave.com] Retrieved June 28, 2015</ref> was an actress. He appeared on the [[Legitimate theater|legitimate]] stage as a child, and played throughout the United States and in [[London]]. He appeared in silent films, and was the director of popular one-act plays at New York's [[Princess Theatre, New York City|Princess Theatre]].
In 1900, he appeared in London in ''[[Ib and Little Christina]]''. His Broadway stage successes include ''[[The Duchess of Dantzic]]'' (1903, as Napoleon), ''Salvation Nell'' (1908) in a breakout performance as the brutish husband of [[Mrs. Fiske]], ''Within the Law'' (1912), ''Molière'' (1919), ''[[A Woman of No Importance]]'' (1916), ''[[The Lady of the Camellias]]'' (1917), and ''Getting Together'' (1918). [[File:Holbrook Blinn 2.jpg|left|200px|thumb|'''Holbrook Blinn''' as Chief Rain-In-The-Face, in the play "The Great Silence (Sunset Magazine, Nov. 1905 -April, 1906)]] Some of his finest silent screen accomplishments are in ''[[McTeague (film)|McTeague]]'' (1916), ''[[The Bad Man (1923 film)|The Bad Man]]'' (1923), ''[[Rosita (film)|Rosita]]'' (1923), ''[[Yolanda (film)|Yolanda]]'' (1924), and ''[[Janice Meredith (film)|Janice Meredith]]'' (1924), the latter two films both starring [[Marion Davies]].
==Death== [[File:Holbrook Blinn Gravesite 2010.JPG|thumb|right|The gravesite of Holbrook Blinn]]Blinn died from complications of a fall off his horse near Journey's End, his [[Croton-on-Hudson, New York]] home, and is buried in [[Sleepy Hollow Cemetery]] in [[Sleepy Hollow, New York]].
